anontext: As she descended the last flight of stairs, she was a good deal startled at seeing a bright light issuing from the kitchen--the door of which was open--much brighter than could possibly proceed from the fire, for the whole passage was illuminated by it.

text: It then occurred to her that possibly something might have caught fire; so half-frightened, she advanced on tip-toe and peeped in, when, to her surprise, she saw a lady dressed in white, sitting by the fire, into which she was sadly and thoughtfully gazing.
